Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libc (>= 1.1.8), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: FUSE userspace utilities
 FUSE (Filesystem in Userspace) is an interface for userspace programs 
 to export a filesystem to the Linux kernel.
 .
 This package provides tools for managing FUSE (Filesystem in Userspace)
 filesystems.

Package: fuse2-dev
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Provides: libfuse2-dev
Depends: libc-dev, fuse2 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: FUSE development headers and static libraries
 This package provides static libraries, pkgconfig data and header files 
 required for development using FUSE.

